# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Folio — .gitignore
# Repo is public from day one.
# Principle: commit the RESULT and what's needed to build/run/understand it.
# Ignore (a) private design process and (b) regenerable tooling installs.
# NOTE: .gitignore has no inline comments — keep comments on their own lines.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Private design process & working artefacts (internal thinking) ---
# brief, PRD, architecture, epics, decision memlogs — process, not result
/_bmad-output/
# Flow orchestration workspace & run state
/.flow/

# --- Regenerable tooling installs (reinstall, don't commit) ---
# BMAD framework — restore with: npx bmad-method install
/_bmad/
# Claude Code project config + installed skills (personal/internal)
/.claude/
# Flow hired-team personas — orchestration state, not a build artefact
/team/

# --- Secrets & local env (never commit) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# wrangler / Cloudflare local secrets
.dev.vars
# Cloudflare Workers local state
.wrangler/
*.local

# --- Node / build outputs ---
node_modules/
dist/
build/
coverage/
*.log

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
